Draw a grid.

This function draws a grid with its corner and the origin (0,0,0) extending
in the positive x and y-directions. The center of the grid is at the point
`(x/2, y/2)`.

{:alert.alert-info}
To draw a grid centered at the origin use the batch rendering method
[at](/documentation/rendering/batch-mode.html#at).

### syntax

~~~ python
grid(x, y, nx, ny)
~~~

### parameters

x  | length of the grid in the x-direction
y  | length of the grid in the y-direction
nx | number of cells in the x-direction
ny | number of cells in the y-direction


